5|$|Aqua regia, {{a mixture}} {{consisting}} of hydrochloric and nitric acids, prepared by dissolving <b>sal</b> <b>ammoniac</b> in nitric acid, {{was described in}} the works of Pseudo-Geber, a 13th-century European alchemist. Other references suggest that the first mention of aqua regia is in Byzantine manuscripts dating {{to the end of the}} 13th century.|$|E
